article.headline: Lamar 118, St. Gregory's 69
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- Charlie Harper scored 17 points to lead seven players in double figures as Lamar blasted NAIA opponent St. Gregory's 118-69 Saturday night. Anthony Miles scored 15 for the Cardinals (4-2), followed by Mike James with 14, Kendrick Harris and Brandon Davis with 13 each, Orlando Brazier with 11 and Vincenzo Nelson with 10. Fayzon Richey led St. Gregory's with 18 points. The Cavaliers, an NAIA Division I university from Shawnee, Okla., designated the game as an exhibition. Their record stands at 3-4. Lamar outscored St. Gregory's 63-30 in the second half.
